30#include <sys/types.h>
31
32#include <assert.h> /* NO_CHECK_STYLE */
33#include <signal.h>
34#include <stdio.h>
35#include <stdlib.h>
36#include <string.h>
37#include <unistd.h>
38
39static
40int
41h_echo(const char *msg)
42{
43 printf("%s\n", msg);
44 return EXIT_SUCCESS;
45}
46
47static
48int
49h_exit_failure(void)
50{
51 return EXIT_FAILURE;
52}
53
54static
55int
56h_exit_signal(void)
57{
58 kill(getpid(), SIGKILL);
59 assert(0); /* NO_CHECK_STYLE */
60 return EXIT_FAILURE;
61}
62
63static
64int
65h_exit_success(void)
66{
67 return EXIT_SUCCESS;
68}
69
70static
71int
72h_stdout_stderr(const char *id)
73{
74 fprintf(stdout, "Line 1 to stdout for %s\n", id);
75 fprintf(stdout, "Line 2 to stdout for %s\n", id);
76 fprintf(stderr, "Line 1 to stderr for %s\n", id);
77 fprintf(stderr, "Line 2 to stderr for %s\n", id);
78
79 return EXIT_SUCCESS;
80}
81
82static
83void
84check_args(const int argc, const char *const argv[], const int required)
85{
86 if (argc < required) {
87 fprintf(stderr, "Usage: %s helper-name [args]\n", argv[0]);
88 exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
89 }
90}
91
92int
93main(int argc, const char *const argv[])
94{
95 int exitcode;
96
97 check_args(argc, argv, 2);
98
99 if (strcmp(argv[1], "echo") == 0) {
100 check_args(argc, argv, 3);
101 exitcode = h_echo(argv[2]);
102 } else if (strcmp(argv[1], "exit-failure") == 0)
103 exitcode = h_exit_failure();
104 else if (strcmp(argv[1], "exit-signal") == 0)
105 exitcode = h_exit_signal();
106 else if (strcmp(argv[1], "exit-success") == 0)
107 exitcode = h_exit_success();
108 else if (strcmp(argv[1], "stdout-stderr") == 0) {
109 check_args(argc, argv, 3);
110 exitcode = h_stdout_stderr(argv[2]);
111 } else {
112 fprintf(stderr, "%s: Unknown helper %s\n", argv[0], argv[1]);
113 exitcode = EXIT_FAILURE;
114 }
115
116 return exitcode;
117}
